The map is enclosed in a single, breathtakingly cold border befitting the immortal queen. Its outermost edge is a hairline of frosted, spell‑silver, so fine it seems to shimmer with its own inner light. Inside runs a continuous register of stylised, interlocking snowflake‑and‑ice‑crystal motifs, rendered in raised, translucent white and pale cyan lacquer, each crystal facet catching an imaginary, auroral light. Interwoven with the crystals are the delicate silhouettes of soaring snow‑phoenixes and the sweeping, wing‑like arcs of the aurora itself. At the four corners, the border transforms into ornate, winter‑themed compass medallions: a great, eight‑pointed crystalline halo (northwest), a snow‑phoenix in full stoop (northeast), a frozen, shattering glacial spike (southwest), and the floating ice‑star weapon, its centre a glowing, icy blue core (southeast). The innermost edge is a soft, wet‑brush enso of lavender‑grey sumi, its edges bleeding like a whisper of frost on glass — a meditation on immortality, isolation, and the cold, patient power of the North.

5. THE LANDSCAPE — ZOOMED‑IN, HYPER‑DETAILED QUEEN’S PEAK
The peak and its immediate surroundings are a breathtaking, frozen tapestry of celestial light, ancient stone, and a single, regal, solitary presence.

