The Glacial Ascent (The Path of the Queen): The mountain’s lower slopes are a labyrinth of jagged, blue‑white ice ridges and deep, hidden crevasses, rendered in sharp, angular dry‑brush strokes. A single, barely visible, winding path — the Path of the Queen — spirals upward, marked by ancient, frozen stone lanterns that glow with a faint, cold cyan light. No living creature traverses it; it is a road for memory and myth.

The Ice Palace (The Frozen Throne): At the very summit, cradled by the highest, most jagged spires of the peak, sits the Ice Palace, Aurora’s sanctuary of solitude. It is not a fortress, but a delicate, impossibly beautiful structure of crystalline ice and frozen starlight. Its walls are translucent, glowing with a soft, internal cyan‑white light, and its spires are needle‑thin, curving upward like frozen flames. The palace is built around a central, open‑air Throne Platform, a single, massive, carved block of clear, blue‑white ice that serves as the Queen’s seat of observation. The platform overlooks the entire North, the Frozen Sea to the west, and the Megalith Wasteland to the south.

Aurora — The Queen of the North (Tiny, Regal Silhouette): Standing upon the Throne Platform, her form rendered with exquisite, miniature precision, is Aurora herself. She is the immortal, the elemental, the Queen of the North. Her silhouette captures the essence of the description:

