Her hair is a voluminous, flowing mane of platinum white with silvery‑blue undertones, cascading over one shoulder in long, wavy locks that reach past her waist.

Behind her head floats the magnificent crystalline halo, an intricate, eight‑pointed star of translucent, light blue ice‑like shards, radiating outward like a frozen sun. It is rendered as a delicate, luminous ring of silver and pale cyan.

Her upper body is clad in a sophisticated, form‑fitting bodice of deep royal blue and translucent, icy crystal. The high collar and the glowing, six‑pointed star at her chest are suggested by the faintest, precise silver lines. Her sleeves end in dramatic, flared cuffs of jagged ice‑crystal, extending over her hands.

Her lower body is defined by a floor‑length, mermaid‑style gown of midnight blue that transitions to translucent crystalline blue at the hem. The skirt erupts into a series of sharp, geometric ice shards around her feet, as if she is constantly freezing the ground beneath her.

From her shoulders flows the massive, multi‑tiered crystalline cape, behaving like a set of wings. It is composed of several broad, angular, translucent light‑blue panels, layered and sharp, the longest sections reaching toward the floor. The large, rotating crystalline star at her back anchors the cape.

At her side, hovering obediently, is her weapon — a large, floating crystalline ice‑star, roughly the size of a buckler, with a hollow centre and razor‑sharp edges, pulsating with a cold, celestial aura.

Her posture is one of commanding, absolute stillness. She stands as a statue, surveying the frozen world she has watched for millennia. A tiny vermilion label floats beside the throne.

The Aurora Borealis (The Celestial Fire): The entire sky above the peak is dominated by the Aurora Borealis, a permanent, divine ribbon of translucent cyan, violet, and emerald light that pours down from the heavens. It is rendered in sweeping, layered washes of luminous colour, its edges bleeding softly into the twilight sky. The aurora seems to originate from the very tip of the palace’s highest spire, cascading outward like a celestial waterfall.

The Distant Megalith Wasteland: Far below, at the bottom edge of the canvas, the faint, jagged silhouettes of the Megalith Wasteland can be seen — a graveyard of towering stone spires and the distant, crimson‑ochre stain of the ancient battlefields.

