7. JAPANESE CALLIGRAPHY — POETIC TITLE & INVOCATION
At the top‑centre of the map, floating within a reserved patch of aurora‑lit sky, is a bold, vertical column of Japanese calligraphy in gyōsho script, using an ink of amethyst‑flecked silver that shimmers with arcane light. Directly below it, a tiny vermilion woodblock‑stamp English translation appears in delicate brackets:

魔法の学び舎 — 北の尖塔
[Abode of Magic — Northern Spire]

To the right, two smaller columns read:

星の如き教授、雷を纏う副長、紫の妖精が舞う
